rComments: Honestly these reviews are from people who didn't go to class. Yes the material is boring, but this prof is very knowledgeable and listening to the lecture isn't tough. Also, the assignments are fairly straight forward if you do your notes and put some effort towards the class. The presentation is informal and an easy mark! Overall a good class.
Lectures are extremely boring/unengaging and the material on the exam is not what is covered in class so be prepared for some surprises. Honestly, you're better off just reading the book.

The worst! She does not teach and cannot lecture (although she has the knowledge) but it is the biggest torture to listen to her pointless and irrelevant experiences. You don't learn anything from her, you have to read the book to pass. Not clear about the assignment expectations and a VERY TOUGH grader.

Avoid. Spent the entire second half of the semester hearing groups present the same unions and employers over and over and over again. She barely teaches, and her content is dry and painful to sit through. It's sad because this could have been such a great class...
This Prof is Boring to listen To, is very political with her lectures, can not teach effectively and uses a vague test questions. Avoid at all costs.
She is not a good lecturer or teacher in general. Her lectures tend to go off-topic because she spends so much time talking about her own experience in the workforce and her opinions.

Terrible Prof. Very knowledgeable on the subject but lectures are completely un-stimulating. Little/no information on slides or instructions for assignments. Only explains her expectations after we handed in the assignments. Very hard, subjective marker. Midterm & final were MC so just study from the textbook. Try to avoid!

absolutely awful. approached her after class to discuss presentation and paper, did not receive any useful feedback. Her rubrics don't specify what she wants and she doesn't state what she wants from students until AFTER. Horrible prof.... sucks that she's the only one teaching ADM3334.
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Get ready to read', 'Tough grader']

rComments: TERRIBLE prof and lecturer- has the knowledge but not the delivery- is extremely dry and often seemed to get bored with the subject herself.  Met with her once outside of class and she was extremely unhelpful. She also added 20 more MC to the midterm than promised. Tough presentation marker and tough midterm- read the book, no one went to class

I dropped the class because of her. She gives so much attitude when you answer a false question during class. The midterm reflected stuff we never saw in class. I read literally the whole book during reading week but she still managed to put tough questions on the midterm.  really really bad teacher!

Buy the textbook, it's essential to passing as her powerpoints have close to nothing on them and her lectures are boring. She's monotone and the projects are extremely long as the midterm and final are 100+ MCQs. She does however answer e-mails very quickly but her french background is clearly a huge obstacle when she writes or talks.

Midterm was quite easy; the development questions were very vague, which was good in the sense that you could basically write what you remembered, so wasn't asking you very specific things. Big work load with 2 projects. Most of the material was taught by students, so if you don't learn well from textbooks, avoid, but otherwise, easy-ish class.
She yawns all the time. Midterm doesn't reflect what was taught in class. Projects are way too exhaustive. Avoid if possible
Very strict, not approchable, not helpfull at all, she enjoys to complicate the theories.Worse teacher but interesting class
Worst. Midterm is VERY long and hard. She is not approachable, very strict and prepare to be stressed :)
